sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: c2 P22
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: c2 repressor from Salmonella phage P22 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The P22 c2 repressor protein coding sequence is a 720 base-pair sequence with the standard RBS-compatible BioBrick prefix and the standard BioBrick suffix sections on its ends. It binds to the P22 c2 regulatory sequence, BBa_R0053. The sequence contains a LVA tag for faster degredation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
[Note: This is the same part as R0051 except that the -10 and -35 sites and spacing have been changed to comply with BBa_S0001].

The cI regulated promoter is based on the pR promtoer from bacteriohage lambda. The promoter has two two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription. The specific sequence used here is based on the cI repressible promoter used in the Elowitz repressilator (and references therein).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
In order to address concerns about the promoter transcribing in the reverse direction, we have removed the -35 and -10 signals responsible for the promoter activity in the reverse direction. (More details needed here! DE, 2/24/03)

Modified to comply with BBa_S0001:
TTGACA-17N-GATACT

Incompatible with host expressing cI repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator:
Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: aiiA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: autoinducer inactivation enzyme from Bacillus; hydrolyzes acetyl homoserine lactone
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
AF196486 from Bacillus sp. 240B1 putative metallohydrolase (aiiA) gene.
Dong,Y.H., Xu,J.L., Li,X.Z. and Zhang,L.H.: AiiA, an enzyme that inactivates the acylhomoserine lactone quorum-sensing signal and attenuates the virulence of Erwinia
carotovora, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. 97 (7), 3526-3531 (2000).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the autoinducer inactivation enzyme A (aiiA) LVA tagged. The gene was originally isolated from Bacillus sp. 240B1 and it encodes an enzyme that catalyzes the degradation of N-acyl homoserine lactones (AHLs)--quorum sensing autoinducers.
